<h2>Animation/Transition Settings</h2>
<p>Animation/Transition Settings are the core values that define animations and transitions within the Bolt design system. These settings include values such as animation duration, timing functions, and delays.</p>

<div style="padding: 2rem">
  <h2>Durations: <button id="durations-demo-trigger">Trigger</button></h2>
  <p>Duration is how long an animation or transition takes from beginning to end.</p>
  <div id="durations-demo">
    <div class="demo-animated-bar demo-animated-bar--with-slider demo-animated-bar--duration-xfast"><strong>Extra Fast: 0.2s</strong> (Hover or Trigger)</div>
    <div class="demo-animated-bar demo-animated-bar--with-slider demo-animated-bar--duration-fast"><strong>Fast: 0.5s</strong> (Hover or Trigger)</div>
    <div class="demo-animated-bar demo-animated-bar--with-slider demo-animated-bar--duration-medium"><strong>Medium: 1s</strong> (Hover or Trigger)</div>
    <div class="demo-animated-bar demo-animated-bar--with-slider demo-animated-bar--duration-slow"><strong>Slow: 1.5s</strong> (Hover or Trigger)</div>
    <div class="demo-animated-bar demo-animated-bar--with-slider demo-animated-bar--duration-xslow"><strong>Extra Slow: 2.3s</strong> (Hover or Trigger)</div>
  </div>
